Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.80,0:00:14.39,Note,Lelouch/OS,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}a.t.b. stands for Ascension Throne Britannia. Koureki (Holy Calender) is used to represent a.t.b.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.22,0:00:14.31,Default,Lelouch/OS,0000,0000,0000,,a.t.b. 2009, Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.09,0:00:16.19,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Shinto shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.19,0:00:18.56,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Japanese version of a church.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.56,0:00:21.88,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Pope the Emperor of Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.32,0:00:25.89,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,No, Japan doesn't have an Emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.89,0:00:28.60,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,The person who gets selected during an election becomes the Prime Minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.11,0:00:32.95,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,It's only by coincidence that Prime Minister\NKururugi's personal residence is a Shinto shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.69,0:00:37.12,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.12,0:00:39.83,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,These stairs seem to be fairly long.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.83,0:00:42.09,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,This is nothing. I can handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.89,0:00:46.45,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, those stairs were torture to my nine-year-old self.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.12,0:00:53.68,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1000)}However, back then, I absolutely would not let any Japanese person touch Nunnally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.08,0:01:02.90,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,The place we were given to live in was just a small storeroom within the Kururugi Shinto shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.95,0:01:08.16,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,I was momentarily speechless when I first saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.60,0:01:12.13,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, are we there yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.13,0:01:13.96,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.40,0:01:16.21,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of room is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.21,0:01:18.97,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,How's the new home for Brother and I?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.21,0:01:20.75,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,It's a wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.22,0:01:26.07,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,The walls are white like snow, and there are windows with flower decorations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.07,0:01:28.70,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like Elder Sister Euphie's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.70,0:01:31.11,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But it's a bit small.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.11,0:01:32.66,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,But, since it's just Nunnally and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.50,0:01:34.32,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.50,0:01:37.51,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,You over there, come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.58,0:01:39.96,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Don't speak so arrogantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:45.71,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,This was originally my room after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:47.16,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:50.30,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Britannians are so shameless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:53.38,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Do you intend to colonize Japan too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.38,0:01:55.95,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Japan is trying to enforce dominance as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.34,0:01:58.36,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,You enforce sanctions on countries you deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.36,0:01:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.25,0:02:03.35,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Japan and Britannia aren't that different from each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.56,0:02:04.19,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.19,0:02:05.23,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.23,0:02:07.24,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Try asking your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.24,0:02:08.53,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,You're a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.84,0:02:10.29,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about white walls?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.73,0:02:13.28,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the decorated windows in this storeroom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.90,0:02:13.70,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.89,0:02:16.96,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,I charged towards that boy without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:18.28,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.85,0:02:22.17,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,I was no match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.07,0:02:27.15,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,I was defeated just like that, collapsing at his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.80,0:02:30.81,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,How's that, you Britannian bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.12,0:02:33.19,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look down on the Japanese!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.19,0:02:35.48,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,S-Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:37.80,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,You barbarian!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:39.00,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.33,0:02:44.01,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who you are, but I'll do anything you tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.69,0:02:49.15,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,You... Don't tell me you can't see?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:53.61,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, so please don't be alarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.08,0:02:56.46,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.06,0:02:59.77,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,be it fighting or running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.84,0:03:01.67,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:04.31,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.05,0:03:08.33,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,He started to tremble and look around frantically.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:09.06,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.58,0:03:10.93,Default,Suzaku,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:15.75,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,He dashed out of the storeroom as if he were escaping from something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.14,0:03:19.87,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.87,0:03:20.79,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.75,0:03:23.35,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Nunnally, I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.81,0:03:25.56,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.12,0:03:27.69,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:29.23,Default,Nunnally,0000,0000,0000,,He sounded like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.94,0:03:32.27,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely... Kururugi Suzaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.08,0:03:34.92,Default,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,Prime Minister Kururugi's child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:38.21,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,That was my first encounter with Suzaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.08,0:03:43.67,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,To me, who was always surrouned by rivals and vassals, he was my first friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.15,0:03:44.95,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,And eventually...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.77,0:03:47.92,Italics,Lelouch,0000,0000,0000,,he would become the man who was my worst enemy.
